SIMPLE: flapper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flapper
<hw>Flap"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, flaps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Flipper</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>flapper</xex> of a porpoise.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Buckley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A flat object used to make a flapping noise by
striking another object.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A flat and broad object hanging from a larger
object, either flexible like rubber or hinged to allow a swinging
motion; a flap.</def></p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A young woman who dresses in a modern, stylish
manner and behaves unconventionally in social situations; -- a term used
especially to refer to young women during the 1920's and their peculiar
style of dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Flapper skate</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
European skate (<spn>Raia intermedia</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flare</ent>⟦br⟧
